<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 30 at 4:19PM CDT  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central Jim
Hogg and northeastern Zapata Counties through 445 PM CDT...
At 418 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Thompsonville, or 17 miles northeast of Bustamante, moving nortwest
at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Thompsonville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
